        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 11:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They are apparently included under the more general term Nethinim in such passages as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They have been traditionally understood to be the descendants of those inhabitants of the land ‘that were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites and the Jebusites’ of whom Solomon had hired ‘bondservants’ for the work of building his temple (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 5:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
